</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>The pinkie side of your hands should be toward your rib cage.</li><li>The underhand grip should feel natural; your wrists should be in a comfortable position.</li><li>Keep your upper arms very close to your rib cage while lowering and raising the weight.</li><li>This isn’t intended to be a triceps exercise. Squeeze your chest, keeping it tight through the entire exercise.</li><li>The lowest point in the exercise is with hands just in front of the lower rib cage. Bringing the hands any deeper than that stretches the shoulder muscles too much and invites injury.</li></ul>
<h4>The Cable Chest Press</h4>
<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
