<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>Stand facing the cable machine, just a short step away from it.</li><li>Select your handle of choice: straight bar, V-bar, rope, EZ Curl attachment. The key is comfortable hand position.<ul><li>The triceps share a single tendon. Changing your hand position will not emphasize different heads of the triceps. Keeping your wrists in comfortable alignment will allow you to target the triceps appropriately.</li></ul></li><li>Hands should be aligned with your forearms throughout, as if you were planning to throw a punch. Don’t let your hands fall back</li></ul>
