</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>Do these using a pair of dumbbells.</li><li>Adjust your bench so that your arms can be fully extended with the dumbbells without them touching the floor.</li><li>Keep upper arms next to your rib cage during the entire motion.</li><li>The dumbbells should travel straight upward and end up somewhere near your waist at the top. If they end up near your shoulders, you’re doing this incorrectly.<ul><li>Another variation (which we’re not describing here) has the arms coming out to the sides at 90° to your body.</li></ul></li></ul>
