</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips”</p>
<ul><li>Do this exercise single-sided.</li><li>Sit at an angle, with the working arm out to your side.</li><li>Pull the cable down using your upper arm so that the finish is with your elbow next to your hip. Squeeze hard before lowering the weight and repeating. &nbsp;<strong>This is the single best exercise to build wide, thick lats.</strong></li><li>Pro tip: doesn’t matter if your grip is up or down; just let your hand follow your forearm on the way down and up.</li></ul>
<h4><strong>The Lat Pull-Down</strong></h4>
