</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>Select a handle that allows the grip of choice.<ul><li>Lat Pull-Downs can be performed with a variety of grips and grip widths: wide grip, medium grip, narrow grip. And each of those can be done overhand or with a neutral grip where the palms face each other.</li><li>We recommend beginners start narrow and go wider as you get stronger.</li></ul></li><li>Avoid using your arms to do the pulling. Elbows should travel down and backward.</li></ul>
<h4><strong>The Scapula Shrug</strong> (Seated Row Shrug)</h4>
<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
