</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>The most convenient cable machine to use is a seated row machine with two cables.<ul><li>If you’ve got two cables, use a handle on each.</li></ul></li><li>Single cables are fine too. If a single-cable machine is what you have, select a wide grip attachment. Straight, angled, or palms-facing grips are all fine.</li><li>Be prepared for the impression that you’re not moving the weights very far. You’re not, but that’s OK. You’re working the muscles between your shoulder blades.</li><li>“Shrug” your shoulder blades together while keeping your arms straight. Don’t move the weight by bending your elbows.<ul><li>The shrug is backwards, not upwards like the traditional shrug.</li></ul></li></ul>
<h3><span id="leg-exercises" class="uag-toc__heading-anchor"></span><strong>Leg Exercises</strong></h3>
<h4><strong>The Back Squat</strong></h4>
