</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” tips:</p>
<ul><li>Learn the move with the upper “loop” handles facing up.<ul><li>Once you get the hang of it, turn the bar over so the loops are down and you use the grips that are at the same level as the weights. Loops “down” allows for a full ROM.</li></ul></li><li>Same as the back squat, stand with heels on small barbell plates to get into the groove and find the “pocket” where the squat form feels more natural and offers a more complete range of motion (ROM).</li><li>Start with the center of the weights aligned with your ankles, or just slightly in front of them.</li></ul>
<h4><strong>Leg Extensions</strong></h4>
