</div></div></div>
</div></div>
<p>“How To” Tips:</p>
<ul><li>Avoid hyperextending your knees at the top. You can stop each rep 5 to 10° shy of legs being completely straight. Completely straightening the legs puts undue stresses on the knees.</li><li>Align your knee with the axle of the machine. An imaginary straight line should pass from the axle through your knees.</li><li>Squeeze the thighs to raise and lower the weight. Leg extensions are not to be kicked.</li></ul>
<h4><strong>Leg Curls</strong></h4>
